external_knowledge:
- The New York Jets is an NFL team;
- The 2023 draft refers to the NFL draft held in 2023;
- A top 3 pick is a player who was selected within the first three picks of their draft round;
- "Selected more than once" means a player was drafted by multiple teams or multiple times by the same team in the 2023 draft.

- 'draft picks' refer to selections made by teams during a draft process;
- 'scouting reports' provide evaluations of players, often including a numerical rating;
- Teams with no draft picks are excluded from the results.

sql:
SELECT team_id, COUNT(pick_id) AS total_picks 
FROM draft_picks 
GROUP BY team_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT team_id) AS total_teams_with_traded_picks
FROM draft_picks
WHERE round = '2' AND pick_number = 55;

external_knowledge:
- "Shone the brightest" refers to players with the highest average yards per game;
- "Alma maters" refers to the colleges the players attended;
- "Plucked from the pool of talent by the draft" refers to whether the players have been drafted.

- "draft history" refers to the record of when and by which team a player was selected in the draft;
- "scouting reports" are evaluations of players' skills and potential, often used to inform draft decisions;
- "average rating" is the mean value of the numerical ratings given by scouts.

- 'Stars of the 2023 draft' refers to players who were selected in the 2023 draft and have high average ratings;
- 'Shining a light' means identifying or highlighting;
- 'Dawn of 2022' refers to the start of the year 2022 (January 1, 2022);
- 'Highly rated by scouts' means having an average rating greater than 80.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(pick_id) AS number_of_picks
FROM draft_picks
WHERE draft_id = (SELECT draft_id FROM drafts WHERE year = '2023');

